{"rightSidebarLinks":[{"id":"radio","title":"radio","subLink":null},{"id":"staticradiobutton","title":"Static Radio button","subLink":[]},{"id":"radiobuttonbaseduponchangingkeyandvaluenames","title":"Radio button Based upon changing key and value names","subLink":[]},{"id":"inlinedisplay","title":"Inline Display","subLink":[]}],"title":"Radio","description":"","validatorType":"validators","validationTypeTitle":"Validators","type":"simple","category":"dynamic-forms","subCategory":"controls","linkTitle":"radio","tabArray":{},"innerHtml":null,"htmlContent":"<div class=\"title-bar\"><p>To create formControl with type radio, you need to mention the formControl name, source and type in the <span class='highlighted'>serverData</span> and pass it in the <span class='highlighted'>formGroup</span> method of <span class='highlighted'>RxDynamicFormBuilder</span>.</p></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'staticradiobutton'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Static Radio button<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/radio/validators#staticradiobutton'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-static-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-static-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-radio-static\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'radiobuttonbaseduponchangingkeyandvaluenames'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Radio button Based upon changing key and value names<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/radio/validators#radiobuttonbaseduponchangingkeyandvaluenames'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >The name of key and value can be changed as per your requirement and they need to be passed in serverData as <span class='highlighted'>textPropName</span> and <span class='highlighted'>valuePropName</span> respectively.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-value-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-value-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-radio-value\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class='row page-section' id= 'inlinedisplay'>\r\n<div class='col-lg-12'>\r\n<h2>Inline Display<a title='Link to this heading' class='link-header' href='/dynamic-forms/radio/validators#inlinedisplay'><i class='fa fa-link'></i></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p class='showHideElement' >If you want to group radio buttons by displaying them inline i.e. in the same horizontal line, then you can set <span class='highlighted'>inline: true</span> for that perticulare formControl in the <span class='highlighted'>serverData</span>. </p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-inline-component\"></div> \r\n<p class='showHideElement' >Next, we need to write html code.</p>\r\n<div component=\"app-code\" key=\"radio-inline-html\"></div> \r\n<div component=\"app-example-runner\" ref-component=\"app-radio-inline\"></div>\r\n</div></div>\r\n"}